Source: libpedalog
Section: libs
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Dan Haughey <dan@powwow-pedal-power.org.uk>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.0), cmake, libusb-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.2
Homepage: https://github.com/powwow-pedal-power/libpedalog
#Vcs-Git: git://git.debian.org/collab-maint/libpedalog.git
#Vcs-Browser: http://git.debian.org/?p=collab-maint/libpedalog.git;a=summary

Package: libpedalog0
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Library for reading data from Pedalog devices
 The Pedalog is a device made by Renewable Energy Innovations
 (http://www.re-innovation.co.uk).  It has been specially
 designed to monitor the power and energy generated by pedal
 powered electricity generators.

Package: libpedalog-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libpedalog0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Library for reading data from Pedalog devices (development files)
 The Pedalog is a device made by Renewable Energy Innovations
 (http://www.re-innovation.co.uk).  It has been specially
 designed to monitor the power and energy generated by pedal
 powered electricity generators.

